        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 2:10PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 209 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rio Hondo High School, or over Rio Hondo, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harlingen, San Benito, Rio Hondo, Palm Valley, Arroyo City,
Brownsville, Primera, Combes, La Encantada Elementary School, and
Doctor Hesiquio Rodriguez Elementary School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
